oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Elite Theatre
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a postcard featuring an image of the exterior of the Elite Theatre in Jackson. Signs at the box office read: "New pictures daily," and "Admission 10 cents, children 5 cents." Text at the bottom of the postcard reads: "Compliments of the Elite Theatre on its first anniversary, January 9th, 1910, Jackson, Tennessee."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Motion picture theaters
